messages.content: ComfyUI-SEGAttention is a set of nodes that use Smoothed Energy Guidance for ComfyUI.
What is the purpose of ComfyUI-SEGAttention?
The purpose of ComfyUI-SEGAttention is to provide nodes that utilize Smoothed Energy Guidance in the ComfyUI interface for generating images.
Where can one find example workflows for ComfyUI-SEGAttention?
Example workflows for ComfyUI-SEGAttention can be found in the `workflow_examples` directory.
What is the link to the Smoothed Energy Guidance repository?
The link to the Smoothed Energy Guidance repository is https://github.com/SusungHong/SEG-SDXL.
What are the file names of the example images provided?
The file names of the example images provided are ComfyUI_temp_fspph_00021_, ComfyUI_temp_fspph_00020_, ComfyUI_temp_fspph_00019_, and ComfyUI_temp_fspph_00006_.
Where are the example images for ComfyUI-SEGAttention hosted?
The example images for ComfyUI-SEGAttention are hosted on the user-attachments GitHub repository.
How many example images are provided for ComfyUI-SEGAttention?
There are four example images provided for ComfyUI-SEGAttention.
